    <fr:title text="Earlier and Brzozowski derivatives">Earlier and Brzozowski derivatives</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>On grammars, the <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FO/" title="Earlier on presheaves" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FO/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FO/" type="local">earlier</fr:link> modality is a sum over proper
extensions of the input:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\lhd  X\right )\mathclose {}}\,{\mathopen {}\left (v\right )\mathclose {}} = \sum _{w \neq  \varepsilon } X\,{\mathopen {}\left (w \cdot  v\right )\mathclose {}}.]]></fr:tex>
Writing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D_w]]></fr:tex> for the <html:em>Brzozowski derivative</html:em>,
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (D_w B\right )\mathclose {}}\,{\mathopen {}\left (v\right )\mathclose {}} = B\,{\mathopen {}\left (w \cdot  v\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, this says
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lhd  X = \bigoplus _{w \neq  \varepsilon } D_w X]]></fr:tex>: earlier is the total
derivative.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
