            <fr:title text="Earlier on presheaves">Earlier on presheaves</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p><fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" title="Later on presheaves" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" type="local">Later</fr:link> takes a <html:em>limit</html:em> over smaller indices. Dually,
the <html:em>earlier</html:em> modality takes a colimit over larger indices: an
element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lhd  P]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>-element sitting at some object
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> strictly above <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, carried down along a chosen morphism
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \to  y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Earlier is left adjoint to later:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\lhd  \dashv  \rhd ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>Under this adjunction, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {next} : P \to  \rhd  P]]></fr:tex> corresponds to
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathsf {prev} : \lhd  P \to  P,]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
